{
  "texts": [
    "The polyp axes range from 8 and 119 pixels assuming an elliptical form with a 3/2 major to minor axes ratio.",
    "The median polyp area is 2440 pixels, while the mean polyp area is 3122 pixels.",
    "The authors use a scanning window of 120 × 120 pixels in size since the great majority of polyps have an area of fewer than 10,000 pixels (Figure 22).",
    "In the experiments, (El Khatib et al. 2015) display some statistics on the polyps detected in nine of the database's short videos (3477 frames with polyps).",
    "Jha et al. (2021b) used all 20 videos for experimentation while training, validation, and testing with an 80:10:10 split on the database ASU-Mayo."
  ]
}